15 shall must separate the appropriations for full-time equivalent positions as defined in
16 subdivision 2-14-2(12) § 2-14-2.
17 Section 6. That § 9-2-7 be AMENDED:
18 9-2-7. For the purpose of dividing a municipality into wards, the number of
19 inhabitants is determined by subdivision 2-14-2(20) population, as defined in § 2-14-2.
20 The governing body may, by resolution, authorize the finance officer to determine the
21 number of inhabitants by filing a certificate showing the number of persons individuals
22 registered to vote in each ward of the municipality. That number multiplied by two
23 constitutes the number of inhabitants until the next federal census is completed.
24 Section 7. That § 13-49-14.11 be AMENDED:
