6 Section 8. That § 29A-5-102 be AMENDED:
7 29A-5-102. Terms used in this chapter mean:
8 (1) "Absentee," any individual who has disappeared, who has been forcibly detained
9 either illegally or by a foreign power, or who is otherwise located in a foreign
10 country and is unable to return;
11 (2) "Conservator," one appointed by the court to be responsible for managing the
12 estate and financial affairs of a minor or protected person;
13 (3) "Court representative," any individual appointed by the court to make
14 investigations and recommendations as provided in this chapter or as otherwise
15 ordered by the court;
16 (4) "Guardian," one appointed by the court to be responsible for the personal affairs
17 of a minor or protected person, but excludes one who is merely a guardian ad
18 litem;
19 (5) "Interested person," any individual who is the subject of a guardianship or
20 conservatorship proceeding, and any entity, public agency, or other individual with
21 an interest in the proceeding, either generally or as to a particular matter;
22 (6) "Limited conservator," one appointed by the court who has only those
23 responsibilities for managing the estate and financial affairs of a minor or protected
24 person as are specified in the order of appointment;
25 (7) "Limited guardian," one appointed by the court who has only those responsibilities
26 for the personal affairs of a minor or protected person as are specified in the order
27 of appointment;
28 (8) "Minor," any individual under eighteen years of age;
29 (9) "Person alleged to need protection," any individual for whom the appointment of a
30 guardian or conservator is being sought other than for reasons of minority;
31 (10) "Protected person," any individual for whom a guardian or conservator has been
32 appointed other than for reasons of minority.
33 Unless the context otherwise requires, anyAny reference to a "guardian" includes
34 a "limited guardian," and any reference to a "conservator" includes a "limited
Underscores indicate new language.
Overstrikes indicate deleted language.

