1 conservator." Any reference to a "conservator" also includes," or a guardian with authority
2 to manage the estate and financial affairs of a minor or protected person who was
3 appointed prior to July 1, 1993. Any reference to a "person" refers to either an "interested
4 person," a "person alleged to need protection," or a "protected person," as the context
5 requires, and but does not refer to a "person" as defined in § 2-14-2(18).
6 Section 9. That § 32-5-2 be AMENDED:
7 32-5-2. Every owner, or with written authorization, any other person, as defined
8 by subdivision 2-14-2(18) in § 2-14-2, on behalf of and as the agent for the owner, of a
9 motor vehicle, motorcycle, truck tractor, road tractor, trailer or semitrailer, or recreational
10 vehicle or trailer, which is operated or driven upon the public highways of this state, shall,
11 except as otherwise expressly provided, present to the county treasurer of the owner's
12 county, or, in case of a nonresident of this state, the treasurer of any county, application
13 for the registration of that vehicle. The application form shall must be furnished by the
14 department and shall contain but not be limited to at least the following information:
15 (1) The number of cylinders or the bore and stroke of each cylinder;
16 (2) The manufacturer's weight;
17 (3) Whether the vehicle operates on diesel fuel, liquified petroleum gas, gasoline, or
18 any other special fuel;
19 (4) The make, model, body, year, color, and vehicle identification number of the
20 vehicle;
21 (5) The odometer reading; and
22 (6) The purchase price and the name and address of the seller, buyer, and any
23 lienholder, if any.
24 Any person who fails to provide the above information to the county treasurer or
25 the department is guilty of a Class 2 misdemeanor. The department or the county
26 treasurer may not accept an incomplete application form or an application form which that
27 the department considers erroneous.
